Data processing

Initial Data File

This dataset contains records of syringe collection in New York Citys Parks, gathered jointly by NYC Parks staff and partner organizations including Washington Heights Corner Project and New York Harm Reduction Educators. The dataset is part of NYC Parks Syringe Litter Data Collection initiative and is publicly accessible through the NYC OpenData (Map data), demonstrating the citys commitment to transparency in public health and safety data. Daily collection data is compiled and published monthly after thorough quality control processes, making it a reliable source for analyzing syringe disposal patterns in NYC Parks.
